286 // EmitInstrWithCustomInserter - This method should be implemented by targets ----
287 // that mark instructions with the 'usesCustomInserter' flag. These ----
288 // instructions are special in various ways, which require special support to ----

290 // basic blocks, and this method is called to expand it into a sequence of ----

705 SmallPtrSet Added; 0
706 SmallVector Worklist; 0
707 ----
708 Worklist.push_back(CurDAG->getRoot().getNode()); 0

710 ----
711 KnownBits Known; 0
712 ----

715 ----

718 if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::Other && Added.insert(Op.getNode()).second) 0

733 continue; 0

1030 // This function is used to enforce the topological node id property ----
1031 // leveraged during instruction selection. Before the selection process all ----
1032 // nodes are given a non-negative id such that all nodes have a greater id than ----
1033 // their operands. As this holds transitively we can prune checks that a node N ----
1034 // is a predecessor of M another by not recursively checking through M's ----
1035 // operands if N's ID is larger than M's ID. This significantly improves ----
1036 // performance of various legality checks (e.g. IsLegalToFold / UpdateChains). ----
1037 ----
1038 // However, when we fuse multiple nodes into a single node during the ----
1039 // selection we may induce a predecessor relationship between inputs and ----
1040 // outputs of distinct nodes being merged, violating the topological property. ----
1041 // Should a fused node have a successor which has yet to be selected, ----
1042 // our legality checks would be incorrect. To avoid this we mark all unselected ----
1043 // successor nodes, i.e. id != -1, as invalid for pruning by bit-negating (x => ----
1044 // (-(x+1))) the ids and modify our pruning check to ignore negative Ids of M. ----
1045 // We use bit-negation to more clearly enforce that node id -1 can only be ----
1046 // achieved by selected nodes. As the conversion is reversable to the original ----
1047 // Id, topological pruning can still be leveraged when looking for unselected ----
1048 // nodes. This method is called internally in all ISel replacement related ----
1049 // functions. ----
1050 void SelectionDAGISel::EnforceNodeIdInvariant(SDNode *Node) { 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1051 SmallVector Nodes; 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1052 Nodes.push_back(Node); 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1053 ----
1054 while (!Nodes.empty()) { 56 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1055 SDNode *N = Nodes.pop_back_val(); 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1056 for (auto *U : N->uses()) { 64 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1057 auto UId = U->getNodeId(); 36 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1058 if (UId > 0) { 36 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1059 InvalidateNodeId(U); 0
1060 Nodes.push_back(U); 0
1061 } ----
1062 } ----
1063 } ----
1064 } 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1065 ----
1066 // InvalidateNodeId - As explained in EnforceNodeIdInvariant, mark a ----
1067 // NodeId with the equivalent node id which is invalid for topological ----
1068 // pruning. ----
1069 void SelectionDAGISel::InvalidateNodeId(SDNode *N) { 0
1070 int InvalidId = -(N->getNodeId() + 1); 0
1071 N->setNodeId(InvalidId); 0
1072 } 0
1073 ----
1074 // getUninvalidatedNodeId - get original uninvalidated node id. ----
1075 int SelectionDAGISel::getUninvalidatedNodeId(SDNode *N) { 0
1076 int Id = N->getNodeId(); 0
1077 if (Id < -1) 0
1078 return -(Id + 1); 0
1079 return Id; 0
1080 } ----

1189 static bool hasExceptionPointerOrCodeUser(const CatchPadInst *CPI) { 0
1190 for (const User *U : CPI->users()) { 0
1191 if (const IntrinsicInst *EHPtrCall = dyn_cast(U)) { 0
1192 Intrinsic::ID IID = EHPtrCall->getIntrinsicID(); 0
1193 if (IID == Intrinsic::eh_exceptionpointer || 0
1194 IID == Intrinsic::eh_exceptioncode) ----
1195 return true; 0
1196 } ----
1197 } ----
1198 return false; 0
1199 } ----
1200 ----
1201 // wasm.landingpad.index intrinsic is for associating a landing pad index number ----
1202 // with a catchpad instruction. Retrieve the landing pad index in the intrinsic ----
1203 // and store the mapping in the function. ----
1204 static void mapWasmLandingPadIndex(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, 0
1205 const CatchPadInst *CPI) { ----
1206 MachineFunction *MF = MBB->getParent(); 0
1207 // In case of single catch (...), we don't emit LSDA, so we don't need ----
1208 // this information. ----
1209 bool IsSingleCatchAllClause = ----
1210 CPI->arg_size() == 1 && 0
1211 cast(CPI->getArgOperand(0))->isNullValue(); 0
1212 // cathchpads for longjmp use an empty type list, e.g. catchpad within %0 [] ----
1213 // and they don't need LSDA info ----
1214 bool IsCatchLongjmp = CPI->arg_size() == 0; 0
1215 if (!IsSingleCatchAllClause && !IsCatchLongjmp) { 0
1216 // Create a mapping from landing pad label to landing pad index. ----
1217 bool IntrFound = false; 0
1218 for (const User *U : CPI->users()) { 0
1219 if (const auto *Call = dyn_cast(U)) { 0
1220 Intrinsic::ID IID = Call->getIntrinsicID(); 0
1221 if (IID == Intrinsic::wasm_landingpad_index) { 0
1222 Value *IndexArg = Call->getArgOperand(1); 0
1223 int Index = cast(IndexArg)->getZExtValue(); 0
1224 MF->setWasmLandingPadIndex(MBB, Index); 0
1225 IntrFound = true; 0
1226 break; 0
1227 } ----
1228 } ----
1229 } ----
1230 assert(IntrFound && "wasm.landingpad.index intrinsic not found!"); 0
1231 (void)IntrFound; ----
1232 } ----
1233 } 0

1235 /// PrepareEHLandingPad - Emit an EH_LABEL, set up live-in registers, and ----
1236 /// do other setup for EH landing-pad blocks. ----
1237 bool SelectionDAGISel::PrepareEHLandingPad() { 0
1238 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = FuncInfo->MBB; 0
1239 const Constant *PersonalityFn = FuncInfo->Fn->getPersonalityFn(); 0
1240 const BasicBlock *LLVMBB = MBB->getBasicBlock(); 0
1241 const TargetRegisterClass *PtrRC = ----
1242 TLI->getRegClassFor(TLI->getPointerTy(CurDAG->getDataLayout())); 0
1243 ----
1244 auto Pers = classifyEHPersonality(PersonalityFn); 0
1245 ----
1246 // Catchpads have one live-in register, which typically holds the exception ----
1247 // pointer or code. ----
1248 if (isFuncletEHPersonality(Pers)) { 0
1249 if (const auto *CPI = dyn_cast(LLVMBB->getFirstNonPHI())) { 0
1250 if (hasExceptionPointerOrCodeUser(CPI)) { 0
1251 // Get or create the virtual register to hold the pointer or code. Mark ----
1252 // the live in physreg and copy into the vreg. ----
1253 MCPhysReg EHPhysReg = TLI->getExceptionPointerRegister(PersonalityFn); 0
1254 assert(EHPhysReg && "target lacks exception pointer register"); 0
1255 MBB->addLiveIn(EHPhysReg); 0
1256 unsigned VReg = FuncInfo->getCatchPadExceptionPointerVReg(CPI, PtrRC); 0
1257 BuildMI(*MBB, FuncInfo->InsertPt, SDB->getCurDebugLoc(), 0
1258 TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), VReg) 0
1259 .addReg(EHPhysReg, RegState::Kill); 0
1260 } ----
1261 } ----
1262 return true; 0
1263 } ----
1264 ----
1265 // Add a label to mark the beginning of the landing pad. Deletion of the ----
1266 // landing pad can thus be detected via the MachineModuleInfo. ----
1267 MCSymbol *Label = MF->addLandingPad(MBB); 0
1268 ----
1269 const MCInstrDesc &II = TII->get(TargetOpcode::EH_LABEL); 0
1270 BuildMI(*MBB, FuncInfo->InsertPt, SDB->getCurDebugLoc(), II) 0
1271 .addSym(Label); 0
1272 ----
1273 // If the unwinder does not preserve all registers, ensure that the ----
1274 // function marks the clobbered registers as used. ----
1275 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI = *MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1276 if (auto *RegMask = TRI.getCustomEHPadPreservedMask(*MF)) 0
1277 MF->getRegInfo().addPhysRegsUsedFromRegMask(RegMask); 0
1278 ----
1279 if (Pers == EHPersonality::Wasm_CXX) { 0
1280 if (const auto *CPI = dyn_cast(LLVMBB->getFirstNonPHI())) 0
1281 mapWasmLandingPadIndex(MBB, CPI); 0
1282 } else { ----
1283 // Assign the call site to the landing pad's begin label. ----
1284 MF->setCallSiteLandingPad(Label, SDB->LPadToCallSiteMap[MBB]); 0
1285 // Mark exception register as live in. ----
1286 if (unsigned Reg = TLI->getExceptionPointerRegister(PersonalityFn)) 0
1287 FuncInfo->ExceptionPointerVirtReg = MBB->addLiveIn(Reg, PtrRC); 0
1288 // Mark exception selector register as live in. ----
1289 if (unsigned Reg = TLI->getExceptionSelectorRegister(PersonalityFn)) 0
1290 FuncInfo->ExceptionSelectorVirtReg = MBB->addLiveIn(Reg, PtrRC); 0
1291 } ----
1292 ----
1293 return true; 0
1294 } ----

1296 // Mark and Report IPToState for each Block under IsEHa ----
1297 void SelectionDAGISel::reportIPToStateForBlocks(MachineFunction *MF) { 0
1298 MachineModuleInfo &MMI = MF->getMMI(); 0
1299 llvm::WinEHFuncInfo *EHInfo = MF->getWinEHFuncInfo(); 0
1300 if (!EHInfo) 0
1301 return; 0
1302 for (auto MBBI = MF->begin(), E = MF->end(); MBBI != E; ++MBBI) { 0
1303 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = &*MBBI; 0
1304 const BasicBlock *BB = MBB->getBasicBlock(); 0
1305 int State = EHInfo->BlockToStateMap[BB]; 0

1832 // case here doesn't go outside the range. In this case, there is no need ----

1844 NextMBB = BTB.Default; 0

1859 BTB.Cases.pop_back(); 0
1860 break; 0

1999 /// CheckAndMask - The isel is trying to match something like (and X, 255). If ----
2000 /// the dag combiner simplified the 255, we still want to match. RHS is the ----
2001 /// actual value in the DAG on the RHS of an AND, and DesiredMaskS is the value ----
2002 /// specified in the .td file (e.g. 255). ----
2003 bool SelectionDAGISel::CheckAndMask(SDValue LHS, ConstantSDNode *RHS, 0
2004 int64_t DesiredMaskS) const { ----
2005 const APInt &ActualMask = RHS->getAPIntValue(); 0
2006 const APInt &DesiredMask = APInt(LHS.getValueSizeInBits(), DesiredMaskS); 0
2007 ----
2008 // If the actual mask exactly matches, success! ----
2009 if (ActualMask == DesiredMask) 0
2010 return true; 0
2011 ----
2012 // If the actual AND mask is allowing unallowed bits, this doesn't match. ----
2013 if (!ActualMask.isSubsetOf(DesiredMask)) 0
2014 return false; 0
2015 ----
2016 // Otherwise, the DAG Combiner may have proven that the value coming in is ----
2017 // either already zero or is not demanded. Check for known zero input bits. ----
2018 APInt NeededMask = DesiredMask & ~ActualMask; 0
2019 if (CurDAG->MaskedValueIsZero(LHS, NeededMask)) 0
2020 return true; 0
2021 ----
2022 // TODO: check to see if missing bits are just not demanded. ----
2023 ----
2024 // Otherwise, this pattern doesn't match. ----
2025 return false; 0
2026 } 0
2027 ----
2028 /// CheckOrMask - The isel is trying to match something like (or X, 255). If ----
2029 /// the dag combiner simplified the 255, we still want to match. RHS is the ----
2030 /// actual value in the DAG on the RHS of an OR, and DesiredMaskS is the value ----
2031 /// specified in the .td file (e.g. 255). ----
2032 bool SelectionDAGISel::CheckOrMask(SDValue LHS, ConstantSDNode *RHS, 0
2033 int64_t DesiredMaskS) const { ----
2034 const APInt &ActualMask = RHS->getAPIntValue(); 0
2035 const APInt &DesiredMask = APInt(LHS.getValueSizeInBits(), DesiredMaskS); 0
2036 ----
2037 // If the actual mask exactly matches, success! ----
2038 if (ActualMask == DesiredMask) 0
2039 return true; 0
2040 ----
2041 // If the actual AND mask is allowing unallowed bits, this doesn't match. ----
2042 if (!ActualMask.isSubsetOf(DesiredMask)) 0
2043 return false; 0
2044 ----
2045 // Otherwise, the DAG Combiner may have proven that the value coming in is ----
2046 // either already zero or is not demanded. Check for known zero input bits. ----
2047 APInt NeededMask = DesiredMask & ~ActualMask; 0
2048 KnownBits Known = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(LHS); 0
2049 ----
2050 // If all the missing bits in the or are already known to be set, match! ----
2051 if (NeededMask.isSubsetOf(Known.One)) 0
2052 return true; 0
2053 ----
2054 // TODO: check to see if missing bits are just not demanded. ----
2055 ----
2056 // Otherwise, this pattern doesn't match. ----
2057 return false; 0
2058 } 0

2060 /// SelectInlineAsmMemoryOperands - Calls to this are automatically generated ----
2061 /// by tblgen. Others should not call it. ----
2062 void SelectionDAGISel::SelectInlineAsmMemoryOperands(std::vector &Ops, 0
2063 const SDLoc &DL) { ----
2064 std::vector InOps; 0
2065 std::swap(InOps, Ops); 0
2066 ----
2067 Ops.push_back(InOps[InlineAsm::Op_InputChain]); // 0 0
2068 Ops.push_back(InOps[InlineAsm::Op_AsmString]); // 1 0
2069 Ops.push_back(InOps[InlineAsm::Op_MDNode]); // 2, !srcloc 0
2070 Ops.push_back(InOps[InlineAsm::Op_ExtraInfo]); // 3 (SideEffect, AlignStack) 0
2071 ----
2072 unsigned i = InlineAsm::Op_FirstOperand, e = InOps.size(); 0
2073 if (InOps[e-1].getValueType() == MVT::Glue) 0
2074 --e; // Don't process a glue operand if it is here. 0
2075 ----
2076 while (i != e) { 0
2077 unsigned Flags = cast(InOps[i])->getZExtValue(); 0
2078 if (!InlineAsm::isMemKind(Flags) && !InlineAsm::isFuncKind(Flags)) { 0
2079 // Just skip over this operand, copying the operands verbatim. ----
2080 Ops.insert(Ops.end(), InOps.begin()+i, 0
2081 InOps.begin()+i+InlineAsm::getNumOperandRegisters(Flags) + 1); 0
2082 i += InlineAsm::getNumOperandRegisters(Flags) + 1; 0
2083 } else { ----
2084 assert(InlineAsm::getNumOperandRegisters(Flags) == 1 && 0
2085 "Memory operand with multiple values?"); ----
2086 ----
2087 unsigned TiedToOperand; ----
2088 if (InlineAsm::isUseOperandTiedToDef(Flags, TiedToOperand)) { 0
2089 // We need the constraint ID from the operand this is tied to. ----
2090 unsigned CurOp = InlineAsm::Op_FirstOperand; 0
2091 Flags = cast(InOps[CurOp])->getZExtValue(); 0
2092 for (; TiedToOperand; --TiedToOperand) { 0
2093 CurOp += InlineAsm::getNumOperandRegisters(Flags)+1; 0
2094 Flags = cast(InOps[CurOp])->getZExtValue(); 0
2095 } ----
2096 } ----
2097 ----
2098 // Otherwise, this is a memory operand. Ask the target to select it. ----
2099 std::vector SelOps; 0
2100 unsigned ConstraintID = InlineAsm::getMemoryConstraintID(Flags); 0
2101 if (SelectInlineAsmMemoryOperand(InOps[i+1], ConstraintID, SelOps)) 0
2102 report_fatal_error("Could not match memory address. Inline asm" 0
2103 " failure!"); ----
2104 ----
2105 // Add this to the output node. ----
2106 unsigned NewFlags = ----
2107 InlineAsm::isMemKind(Flags) 0
2108 ? InlineAsm::getFlagWord(InlineAsm::Kind_Mem, SelOps.size()) 0
2109 : InlineAsm::getFlagWord(InlineAsm::Kind_Func, SelOps.size()); 0
2110 NewFlags = InlineAsm::getFlagWordForMem(NewFlags, ConstraintID); 0
2111 Ops.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(NewFlags, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
2112 llvm::append_range(Ops, SelOps); 0
2113 i += 2; 0
2114 } 0
2115 } ----
2116 ----
2117 // Add the glue input back if present. ----
2118 if (e != InOps.size()) 0
2119 Ops.push_back(InOps.back()); 0
2120 } 0

2122 /// findGlueUse - Return use of MVT::Glue value produced by the specified ----
2123 /// SDNode. ----
2124 /// ----
2125 static SDNode *findGlueUse(SDNode *N) { 0
2126 unsigned FlagResNo = N->getNumValues()-1; 0
2127 for (SDNode::use_iterator I = N->use_begin(), E = N->use_end(); I != E; ++I) { 0
2128 SDUse &Use = I.getUse(); 0
2129 if (Use.getResNo() == FlagResNo) 0
2130 return Use.getUser(); 0
2131 } ----
2132 return nullptr; 0
2133 } ----

2135 /// findNonImmUse - Return true if "Def" is a predecessor of "Root" via a path ----
2136 /// beyond "ImmedUse". We may ignore chains as they are checked separately. ----
2137 static bool findNonImmUse(SDNode *Root, SDNode *Def, SDNode *ImmedUse, 0
2138 bool IgnoreChains) { ----
2139 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
2140 SmallVector WorkList; 0
2141 // Only check if we have non-immediate uses of Def. ----
2142 if (ImmedUse->isOnlyUserOf(Def)) 0
2143 return false; 0
2144 ----
2145 // We don't care about paths to Def that go through ImmedUse so mark it ----
2146 // visited and mark non-def operands as used. ----
2147 Visited.insert(ImmedUse); 0
2148 for (const SDValue &Op : ImmedUse->op_values()) { 0
2149 SDNode *N = Op.getNode(); 0
2150 // Ignore chain deps (they are validated by ----
2151 // HandleMergeInputChains) and immediate uses ----
2152 if ((Op.getValueType() == MVT::Other && IgnoreChains) || N == Def) 0
2153 continue; 0
2154 if (!Visited.insert(N).second) 0
2155 continue; 0
2156 WorkList.push_back(N); 0
2157 } ----
2158 ----
2159 // Initialize worklist to operands of Root. ----
2160 if (Root != ImmedUse) { 0
2161 for (const SDValue &Op : Root->op_values()) { 0
2162 SDNode *N = Op.getNode(); 0
2163 // Ignore chains (they are validated by HandleMergeInputChains) ----
2164 if ((Op.getValueType() == MVT::Other && IgnoreChains) || N == Def) 0
2165 continue; 0
2166 if (!Visited.insert(N).second) 0
2167 continue; 0
2168 WorkList.push_back(N); 0
2169 } ----
2170 } ----
2171 ----
2172 return SDNode::hasPredecessorHelper(Def, Visited, WorkList, 0, true); 0
2173 } 0

2175 /// IsProfitableToFold - Returns true if it's profitable to fold the specific ----
2176 /// operand node N of U during instruction selection that starts at Root. ----
2177 bool SelectionDAGISel::IsProfitableToFold(SDValue N, SDNode *U, 0
2178 SDNode *Root) const { ----
2179 if (OptLevel == CodeGenOpt::None) return false; 0
2180 return N.hasOneUse(); 0
2181 } ----
2182 ----
2183 /// IsLegalToFold - Returns true if the specific operand node N of ----
2184 /// U can be folded during instruction selection that starts at Root. ----
2185 bool SelectionDAGISel::IsLegalToFold(SDValue N, SDNode *U, SDNode *Root, 0
2186 CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel, ----
2187 bool IgnoreChains) { ----
2188 if (OptLevel == CodeGenOpt::None) return false; 0
2189 ----
2190 // If Root use can somehow reach N through a path that that doesn't contain ----
2191 // U then folding N would create a cycle. e.g. In the following ----
2192 // diagram, Root can reach N through X. If N is folded into Root, then ----
2193 // X is both a predecessor and a successor of U. ----
2194 // ----
2195 // [N*] // ----
2196 // ^ ^ // ----
2197 // / \ // ----
2198 // [U*] [X]? // ----
2199 // ^ ^ // ----
2200 // \ / // ----
2201 // \ / // ----
2202 // [Root*] // ----
2203 // ----
2204 // * indicates nodes to be folded together. ----
2205 // ----
2206 // If Root produces glue, then it gets (even more) interesting. Since it ----
2207 // will be "glued" together with its glue use in the scheduler, we need to ----
2208 // check if it might reach N. ----
2209 // ----
2210 // [N*] // ----
2211 // ^ ^ // ----
2212 // / \ // ----
2213 // [U*] [X]? // ----
2214 // ^ ^ // ----
2215 // \ \ // ----
2216 // \ | // ----
2217 // [Root*] | // ----
2218 // ^ | // ----
2219 // f | // ----
2220 // | / // ----
2221 // [Y] / // ----
2222 // ^ / // ----
2223 // f / // ----
2224 // | / // ----
2225 // [GU] // ----
2226 // ----
2227 // If GU (glue use) indirectly reaches N (the load), and Root folds N ----
2228 // (call it Fold), then X is a predecessor of GU and a successor of ----
2229 // Fold. But since Fold and GU are glued together, this will create ----
2230 // a cycle in the scheduling graph. ----
2231 ----
2232 // If the node has glue, walk down the graph to the "lowest" node in the ----
2233 // glueged set. ----
2234 EVT VT = Root->getValueType(Root->getNumValues()-1); 0
2235 while (VT == MVT::Glue) { 0
2236 SDNode *GU = findGlueUse(Root); 0
2237 if (!GU) 0
2238 break; 0
2239 Root = GU; 0
2240 VT = Root->getValueType(Root->getNumValues()-1); 0
2241 ----
2242 // If our query node has a glue result with a use, we've walked up it. If ----
2243 // the user (which has already been selected) has a chain or indirectly uses ----
2244 // the chain, HandleMergeInputChains will not consider it. Because of ----
2245 // this, we cannot ignore chains in this predicate. ----
2246 IgnoreChains = false; 0
2247 } ----
2248 ----
2249 return !findNonImmUse(Root, N.getNode(), U, IgnoreChains); 0
2250 } ----

2253 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2254 ----
2255 std::vector Ops(N->op_begin(), N->op_end()); 0
2256 SelectInlineAsmMemoryOperands(Ops, DL); 0
2257 ----
2258 const EVT VTs[] = {MVT::Other, MVT::Glue}; 0
2259 SDValue New = CurDAG->getNode(N->getOpcode(), DL, VTs, Ops); 0
2260 New->setNodeId(-1); 0
2261 ReplaceUses(N, New.getNode()); 0
2262 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N); 0
2263 } 0

2265 void SelectionDAGISel::Select_READ_REGISTER(SDNode *Op) { 0
2266 SDLoc dl(Op); 0
2267 MDNodeSDNode *MD = cast(Op->getOperand(1)); 0

2339 ----
2340 void SelectionDAGISel::Select_STACKMAP(SDNode *N) { 0
2341 SmallVector Ops; 0
2342 auto *It = N->op_begin(); 0
2343 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2344 ----
2345 // Stash the chain and glue operands so we can move them to the end. ----
2346 SDValue Chain = *It++; 0
2347 SDValue InGlue = *It++; 0
2348 ----
2349 // operand. ----
2350 SDValue ID = *It++; 0
2351 assert(ID.getValueType() == MVT::i64); 0
2352 Ops.push_back(ID); 0
2353 ----
2354 // operand. ----
2355 SDValue Shad = *It++; 0
2356 assert(Shad.getValueType() == MVT::i32); 0
2357 Ops.push_back(Shad); 0
2358 ----
2359 // Live variable operands. ----
2360 for (; It != N->op_end(); It++) 0
2361 pushStackMapLiveVariable(Ops, *It, DL); 0
2362 ----
2363 Ops.push_back(Chain); 0
2364 Ops.push_back(InGlue); 0
2365 ----
2366 SDVTList NodeTys = CurDAG->getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue); 0
2367 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, TargetOpcode::STACKMAP, NodeTys, Ops); 0
2368 } 0
2369 ----
2370 void SelectionDAGISel::Select_PATCHPOINT(SDNode *N) { 0
2371 SmallVector Ops; 0
2372 auto *It = N->op_begin(); 0
2373 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2374 ----
2375 // Cache arguments that will be moved to the end in the target node. ----
2376 SDValue Chain = *It++; 0
2377 std::optional Glue; 0
2378 if (It->getValueType() == MVT::Glue) 0
2379 Glue = *It++; 0
2380 SDValue RegMask = *It++; 0
2381 ----
2382 // operand. ----
2383 SDValue ID = *It++; 0
2384 assert(ID.getValueType() == MVT::i64); 0
2385 Ops.push_back(ID); 0
2386 ----
2387 // operand. ----
2388 SDValue Shad = *It++; 0
2389 assert(Shad.getValueType() == MVT::i32); 0
2390 Ops.push_back(Shad); 0
2391 ----
2392 // Add the callee. ----
2393 Ops.push_back(*It++); 0
2394 ----
2395 // Add . ----
2396 SDValue NumArgs = *It++; 0
2397 assert(NumArgs.getValueType() == MVT::i32); 0
2398 Ops.push_back(NumArgs); 0
2399 ----
2400 // Calling convention. ----
2401 Ops.push_back(*It++); 0
2402 ----
2403 // Push the args for the call. ----
2404 for (uint64_t I = cast(NumArgs)->getZExtValue(); I != 0; I--) 0
2405 Ops.push_back(*It++); 0
2406 ----
2407 // Now push the live variables. ----
2408 for (; It != N->op_end(); It++) 0
2409 pushStackMapLiveVariable(Ops, *It, DL); 0
2410 ----
2411 // Finally, the regmask, chain and (if present) glue are moved to the end. ----
2412 Ops.push_back(RegMask); 0
2413 Ops.push_back(Chain); 0
2414 if (Glue.has_value()) 0
2415 Ops.push_back(*Glue); 0
2416 ----
2417 SDVTList NodeTys = N->getVTList(); 0
2418 CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT, NodeTys, Ops); 0
2419 } 0

2423 GetVBR(uint64_t Val, const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &Idx) { ----
2424 assert(Val >= 128 && "Not a VBR"); 0
2425 Val &= 127; // Remove first vbr bit. 144 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2426 ----
2427 unsigned Shift = 7; 144 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2428 uint64_t NextBits; ----
2429 do { ----
2430 NextBits = MatcherTable[Idx++]; 144 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2431 Val |= (NextBits&127) << Shift; 144 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2432 Shift += 7; 144 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2433 } while (NextBits & 128); 144 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2434 ----
2435 return Val; 144 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2436 } ----

2492 /// HandleMergeInputChains - This implements the OPC_EmitMergeInputChains ----
2493 /// operation for when the pattern matched at least one node with a chains. The ----
2494 /// input vector contains a list of all of the chained nodes that we match. We ----
2495 /// must determine if this is a valid thing to cover (i.e. matching it won't ----
2496 /// induce cycles in the DAG) and if so, creating a TokenFactor node. that will ----
2497 /// be used as the input node chain for the generated nodes. ----
2498 static SDValue ----
2499 HandleMergeInputChains(SmallVectorImpl &ChainNodesMatched, 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2500 SelectionDAG *CurDAG) { ----
2501 ----
2502 SmallPtrSet Visited; 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2503 SmallVector Worklist; 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2504 SmallVector InputChains; 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2505 unsigned int Max = 8192; 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2506 ----
2507 // Quick exit on trivial merge. ----
2508 if (ChainNodesMatched.size() == 1) 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2509 return ChainNodesMatched[0]->getOperand(0); 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2510 ----
2511 // Add chains that aren't already added (internal). Peek through ----
2512 // token factors. ----
2513 std::function AddChains = [&](const SDValue V) { 0
2514 if (V.getValueType() != MVT::Other) 0
2515 return; 0
2516 if (V->getOpcode() == ISD::EntryToken) 0
2517 return; 0
2518 if (!Visited.insert(V.getNode()).second) 0
2519 return; 0
2520 if (V->getOpcode() == ISD::TokenFactor) { 0
2521 for (const SDValue &Op : V->op_values()) 0
2522 AddChains(Op); 0
2523 } else ----
2524 InputChains.push_back(V); 0
2525 }; 0
2526 ----
2527 for (auto *N : ChainNodesMatched) { 0
2528 Worklist.push_back(N); 0
2529 Visited.insert(N); 0
2530 } ----
2531 ----
2532 while (!Worklist.empty()) 0
2533 AddChains(Worklist.pop_back_val()->getOperand(0)); 0
2534 ----
2535 // Skip the search if there are no chain dependencies. ----
2536 if (InputChains.size() == 0) 0
2537 return CurDAG->getEntryNode(); 0
2538 ----
2539 // If one of these chains is a successor of input, we must have a ----
2540 // node that is both the predecessor and successor of the ----
2541 // to-be-merged nodes. Fail. ----
2542 Visited.clear(); 0
2543 for (SDValue V : InputChains) 0
2544 Worklist.push_back(V.getNode()); 0
2545 ----
2546 for (auto *N : ChainNodesMatched) 0
2547 if (SDNode::hasPredecessorHelper(N, Visited, Worklist, Max, true)) 0
2548 return SDValue(); 0
2549 ----
2550 // Return merged chain. ----
2551 if (InputChains.size() == 1) 0
2552 return InputChains[0]; 0
2553 return CurDAG->getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(ChainNodesMatched[0]), 0
2554 MVT::Other, InputChains); 0
2555 } 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

2557 /// MorphNode - Handle morphing a node in place for the selector. ----
2558 SDNode *SelectionDAGISel:: 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2559 MorphNode(SDNode *Node, unsigned TargetOpc, SDVTList VTList, ----
2560 ArrayRef Ops, unsigned EmitNodeInfo) { ----
2561 // It is possible we're using MorphNodeTo to replace a node with no ----
2562 // normal results with one that has a normal result (or we could be ----
2563 // adding a chain) and the input could have glue and chains as well. ----
2564 // In this case we need to shift the operands down. ----
2565 // FIXME: This is a horrible hack and broken in obscure cases, no worse ----
2566 // than the old isel though. ----
2567 int OldGlueResultNo = -1, OldChainResultNo = -1; 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2568 ----
2569 unsigned NTMNumResults = Node->getNumValues(); 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2570 if (Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-1) == MVT::Glue) { 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2571 OldGlueResultNo = NTMNumResults-1; 0
2572 if (NTMNumResults != 1 && 0
2573 Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-2) == MVT::Other) 0
2574 OldChainResultNo = NTMNumResults-2; 0
2575 } else if (Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-1) == MVT::Other) 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2576 OldChainResultNo = NTMNumResults-1; 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

2579 // that this deletes operands of the old node that become dead. ----

2581 ----
2582 // MorphNodeTo can operate in two ways: if an existing node with the ----
2583 // specified operands exists, it can just return it. Otherwise, it ----
2584 // updates the node in place to have the requested operands. ----
2585 if (Res == Node) { 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2586 // If we updated the node in place, reset the node ID. To the isel, ----
2587 // this should be just like a newly allocated machine node. ----
2588 Res->setNodeId(-1); 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2589 } ----
2590 ----
2591 unsigned ResNumResults = Res->getNumValues(); 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2592 // Move the glue if needed. ----
2593 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_GlueOutput) && OldGlueResultNo != -1 && 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2594 (unsigned)OldGlueResultNo != ResNumResults-1) 0
2595 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, OldGlueResultNo), 0
2596 SDValue(Res, ResNumResults - 1)); ----
2597 ----
2598 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_GlueOutput) != 0) 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2599 --ResNumResults; 0
2600 ----
2601 // Move the chain reference if needed. ----
2602 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_Chain) && OldChainResultNo != -1 && 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2603 (unsigned)OldChainResultNo != ResNumResults-1) 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

2605 SDValue(Res, ResNumResults - 1)); ----

2608 // Uses of the old node with the new one. ----

2610 ReplaceNode(Node, Res); 0
2611 } else { ----
2612 EnforceNodeIdInvariant(Res); 28 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2613 } ----
2614 ----

2707 // Bit 0 stores the sign of the immediate. The upper bits contain the magnitude ----
2708 // shifted left by 1. ----
2709 static uint64_t decodeSignRotatedValue(uint64_t V) { 14 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2710 if ((V & 1) == 0) 14 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2711 return V >> 1; 12 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2712 if (V != 1) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2713 return -(V >> 1); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2714 // There is no such thing as -0 with integers. "-0" really means MININT. ----
2715 return 1ULL << 63; 0

2873 /// \A DAG update listener to keep the matching state ----
2874 /// (i.e. RecordedNodes and MatchScope) uptodate if the target is allowed to ----
2875 /// change the DAG while matching. X86 addressing mode matcher is an example ----
2876 /// for this. ----
2877 class MatchStateUpdater : public SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener ----
2878 { ----
2879 SDNode **NodeToMatch; ----
2880 SmallVectorImpl> &RecordedNodes; ----
2881 SmallVectorImpl &MatchScopes; ----
2882 ----
2883 public: ----
2884 MatchStateUpdater(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDNode **NodeToMatch, 0
2885 SmallVectorImpl> &RN, ----
2886 SmallVectorImpl &MS) ----
2887 : SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener(DAG), NodeToMatch(NodeToMatch), 0
2888 RecordedNodes(RN), MatchScopes(MS) {} 0
2889 ----
2890 void NodeDeleted(SDNode *N, SDNode *E) override { 0
2891 // Some early-returns here to avoid the search if we deleted the node or ----
2892 // if the update comes from MorphNodeTo (MorphNodeTo is the last thing we ----
2893 // do, so it's unnecessary to update matching state at that point). ----
2894 // Neither of these can occur currently because we only install this ----
2895 // update listener during matching a complex patterns. ----
2896 if (!E || E->isMachineOpcode()) 0
2897 return; 0
2898 // Check if NodeToMatch was updated. ----
2899 if (N == *NodeToMatch) 0
2900 *NodeToMatch = E; 0
2901 // Performing linear search here does not matter because we almost never ----
2902 // run this code. You'd have to have a CSE during complex pattern ----
2903 // matching. ----
2904 for (auto &I : RecordedNodes) 0
2905 if (I.first.getNode() == N) 0
2906 I.first.setNode(E); 0
2907 ----
2908 for (auto &I : MatchScopes) 0
2909 for (auto &J : I.NodeStack) 0
2910 if (J.getNode() == N) 0
2911 J.setNode(E); 0
2912 } ----
2913 }; ----
2914 ----
2915 } // end anonymous namespace ----
